author: cbs8
title: Houston Astros get playoff rap from Bun B
text:
HOUSTON (AP) - The Houston Astros have a soundtrack to their first playoff run in a decade.
Texas rapper Bun B dropped a track titled "Crush City" as a nod to the home run hitting prowess of the Astros, who were second in the majors with 230 homers in the regular season.
Bun B, who was half of the acclaimed Port Arthur rap group Underground Kingz, released the song last week, and the team played it at Minute Maid Park before Game 4 of the American League Division Series against the Royals.
Game 5 is Wednesday night in Kansas City.
The track is done over the beat to Tyga's 2011 hit "Rack City."
